data.description: Do you want to live on the legendary West Side, but you don't want to live in a house built in the early 1900's?  This cute and charming rancher was built in 2003, and is quaint and clean and ready for easy main level living!  When you walk in the front door, you're greeted by the open concept living room with a cozy gas fireplace and large windows that let in a bunch of natural light. That area flows into the dining room and large kitchen that has a TON of countertop and cabinet space!  Off of the kitchen, enjoy your morning coffee or evening cocktail on the deck!  This compact and easy to maintain home has 3 generously sized bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms, and a 2 car attached garage. From a location standpoint, you're super close to all the wonderful things the West Side has to offer!  Shopping, dining, hiking, biking...and you're ideally situated between I-25 and Highway 24 so you can get north to Monument or Denver, west to Woodland Park and the mountains...or just head down Uintah and you're right downtown!  Come take a look today!
